==English==
===Noun===
'''conclusion''' (''plural'' '''conclusions''')

#The [[end]], [[finish]], [[close]] or [[last]] [[part]] of something
#The [[outcome]] or [[result]] of a [[process]] or [[act]]
#A [[decision]] reached after careful [[thought]]
#{{logic}} In a [[syllogism]], the [[proposition]] that [[follow]]s as a [[necessary]] [[consequence]] of the [[premises]].

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[conclusie]] (1,2,3,4)
*Finnish: [[tulos]] (2), [[ratkaisu]] (2,3), [[johtopäätös]] (3,4), [[päätelmä]] (3,4)
*German: [[Schluss]] <i>m</i>, [[Ende]] <i>n</i> (1); [[Abschluss]] <i>m</i> (z.B. Vertrag) (2); [[Schlussfolgerung]] <i>f</i>, [[Folgerung]] <i>f</i> (3)
*Japanese: [[結末]](ketsumatsu)、[[結び]](musubi) (1); [[結論]](ketsuron)、[[断定]](hantei) (2)；[[推論(suiron)]] (3)

